package pkg

// Gap test: a trusted pure function with a clean Gobra spec (no acc/*/old) can
// be called from a verified function's spec without triggering an error.
//
// pureCallTransitivelySafe checks the spec AST of transitive callees for
// PAccess, PDeref, and POld nodes.  Those checks fire regardless of whether
// the callee has a body.  The remaining gap is hidden heap-dependence in the
// Silver encoding of a trusted stub whose Gobra spec text appears clean —
// for example, a stub axiomatised at the Silver level to read heap memory
// while its Gobra spec only states an arithmetic postcondition.  That gap is
// inherently undetectable from spec AST nodes alone.
//
// NOTE: there is intentionally NO //:: ExpectedOutput(type_error) annotation
// below.  The absence of an error here documents the current behaviour (Option B:
// allowed with a documented caveat).  A pure function whose Gobra spec DOES
// contain acc/*/old would still be caught; the gap is limited to stubs that
// deliberately hide heap access behind a clean-looking spec.

trusted
pure
ensures ret > 0
func trustedMath(x int) (ret int)

// No error expected — trustedMath has a clean Gobra spec.
requires trustedMath(n) > 0
ensures  ret == 1
decreases
verified
func usesTrusted(n int) (ret int) {
	ret = 1
	return ret
}
